# Working queue

When editing `docs/queue.md`:

- The editorial process (ordering rules, dependency precedence, parallel
  waves) lives in the `doccraft-queue-audit` skill. Follow that skill rather
  than reinventing.
- Keep the **Suggested order** table in sync with story `urgency` / `impact`
  when you reprioritise. `docs/backlog.md` owns the full P-tier tables and
  Status column.
- Rows must link to existing files under `docs/stories/`; add a story file
  (and a row in the backlog's *Story files* table) when introducing a new
  queued item.
- After any `depends_on` edit or meaningful queue reorder, invoke
  `doccraft-queue-audit` in the same turn to keep the graph and tables
  consistent.
